cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.MA, cs.SY, cs.DC 

This paper discusses the challenges and opportunities of dynamic mobile networks, which are highly relevant to the field of computer networking (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the impact of density on various network parameters such as interference, capacity, and energy consumption, which are related to information theory (cs.IT). The use of mobile and nomadic small cells to increase coverage and capacity is a form of mobile agent technology (cs.MA). The paper also discusses the need for adapting network functions and communication protocols, which is related to control systems (cs.SY) and distributed computing (cs.DC).
